        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 10:28PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1028 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 16 miles east of Bottomless Lakes State
Park to 20 miles southwest of Dexter, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Dexter, Hagerman, Lake Arthur, Greenfield and Roswell Correctional
Facility.

This includes Highway 285 between Mile Markers 79 and 95.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
